   },
   "source": [
    "### 2. Problem Statement"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "870785db",
   "metadata": {
    "id": "870785db"
   },
   "source": [
    "Kenya hosts one of the largest refugee populations in sub-Saharan Africa, making effective humanitarian planning essential. However, resource planning is often based on current or historical population data rather than future forecasts, limiting preparedness for sudden increases in refugee arrivals.\n",
    "\n",
    "Key challenges identified from the HDX HAPI dataset include:\n",
    "\n",
    "1. Rapid population changes that increase demand for food, healthcare, shelter, and other essential services.\n",
    "2. Diverse demographic groups with different ages, genders, and vulnerabilities that require tailored support.\n",
    "3. Different population categories (e.g., refugees and asylum seekers) with distinct humanitarian needs.\n",
    "4. Delays in resource deployment, making it difficult to respond quickly to population surges.\n",
    "5. Limited use of historical data for forecasting despite decades of available records.\n",
    "\n",
    "These challenges highlight the need for a machine learning-based forecasting approach to support better resource planning and decision-making for refugee assistance in Kenya."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "68589f20",
   "metadata": {
    "id": "68589f20"
   },
   "source": [
    "### 3. Project Objectives"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "e1d9fc12",
   "metadata": {
    "id": "e1d9fc12"
   },
   "source": [
    "#### 3.1 Primary Objective\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "90f89e36",
   "metadata": {
    "id": "90f89e36"
   },
   "source": [
    "To design, develop, and validate a machine learning forecasting system that predicts Kenya's refugee and asylum-seeker population levels disaggregated by origin country, population group, gender, and age cohort with a forecasting horizon of 6 to 24 months, and to translate these forecasts into quantified humanitarian resource planning recommendations."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "79904035",
   "metadata": {
    "id": "79904035"
   },
   "source": [
    "#### 3.2 Specific Objectives\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "d8129bfc",
   "metadata": {
    "id": "d8129bfc"
   },
   "source": [
    "1. Explore the HDX HAPI Kenya dataset to identify population trends, demographic patterns, and changes over time.\n",
    "2. Create relevant features to improve forecasting performance.\n",
    "3. Develop and compare forecasting models to predict refugee population trends.\n",
    "4. Generate population forecasts by refugee category, age, gender, and country of origin.\n",
    "5. Estimate humanitarian resource needs based on the forecasted population.\n",
    "6. Evaluate model performance using standard forecasting metrics (RMSE, MAE, and MAPE).\n",
    "7. Provide recommendations to support data-driven humanitarian planning and decision-making in Kenya."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "c853695e",
   "metadata": {
    "id": "c853695e"
   },
   "source": [
    "### 4. Data Understanding\n"
   ]
