   "source": [
    "Approximately 44% of observations have zero population counts. This is expected in a highly disaggregated refugee dataset where many demographic combinations may have no recorded individuals during a reporting period. Since zeros occur across multiple groups and are not associated with a specific data quality issue, they were retained as valid observations.\n",
    "\n",
    "Retaining zero values allows the forecasting model to learn both population growth patterns and periods of low or absent population presence, improving its ability to support realistic humanitarian planning."
   ]
